&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Client Routing Specialist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Ernest, we don&#39;t just deliver products, we help create seamless experiences for our customers through planning, communication, and execution. As a Client Routing Specialist, you&#39;ll play a critical role in supporting our transportation operations by coordinating routes, managing fleet-related processes, and ensuring deliveries and pickups are executed efficiently and accurately. Success in this role requires strong organizational skills, attention to detail, and the ability to thrive in a fast-paced environment where customer service and operational excellence go hand in hand.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ELD Maintenance&lt;/strong&gt; – Monitor and maintain electronic logging device (ELD) systems for drivers. We utilize mobile applications to track hours of service, which are maintained and managed through office-based PC systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GPS Maintenance&lt;/strong&gt; – Visually track and monitor drivers through GPS systems. Maintain and update driver and vehicle assignments daily.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Truck Maintenance, Repairs &amp;amp; Preventive Maintenance&lt;/strong&gt; – Coordinate with Penske to schedule preventive maintenance services and repairs. Communicate with drivers regarding all truck-related maintenance activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Returns Deliveries&lt;/strong&gt; – Print, schedule, and log customer return deliveries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Delivery Scheduling &amp;amp; Route Planning&lt;/strong&gt; – Print delivery tickets through SAP and route deliveries based on geographic area and available cubic space on trucks. Prepare final route schedules for the loading team and manage driver schedules accordingly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Delivery Appointment Scheduling&lt;/strong&gt; – Coordinate delivery and pickup appointments as needed via phone and email.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Delivery Monitoring (Open Tickets)&lt;/strong&gt; – Monitor and maintain open delivery tickets within the SAP system. Review and manage open tickets on a weekly basis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Freight Management&lt;/strong&gt; – Arrange the most effective method for shipping freight outside of our delivery area through our network of carriers. Create Bills of Lading (BOLs) and upload signed copies into SAP after carrier pickup.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interdepartmental Communication&lt;/strong&gt; – Communicate and collaborate with internal teams regarding delivery requests, pickups, and transportation-related needs involving our fleet.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan and execute approximately 20 delivery routes per day within a strict two-hour planning window prior to night crew deployment, ensuring accuracy and efficiency under time-sensitive conditions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Navigate and build routes manually using Thomas Guide maps and physical street maps. Routing software and digital navigation tools are not utilized in this role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze product dimensions and pallet configuratio

