&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At Ernest, we believe when people move forward, everything moves forward&lt;/strong&gt;. As a Senior Logistics Manager based in Los Angeles, you’ll play a critical role in keeping our operations running smoothly while leading teams with a people-first mindset. This isn’t just about freight, routes, and efficiencies, it’s about building strong relationships, empowering E-Teamers, and creating solutions that help our customers win. Since 1946, Ernest has grown by putting trust, care, and human connection at the center of everything we do. If you’re energized by leading others, solving complex challenges, and being part of a culture where your voice matters and your growth is supported, you’ll feel right at home here.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior Logistics Manager oversees the daily operations and personnel of our largest distribution center located in the city of Commerce, serving as an extension of the local logistics manager’s role. This position provides leadership, direction, support, and oversight to the Client Logistics Manager, warehouse teams, and drivers, ensuring consistent operations in alignment with company policies, procedures, and standards. While maintaining the same core functional responsibilities as a local logistics manager, this role carries added accountability for coordination, operational consistency, and overall facility oversight.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EXPECTATIONS AND GOALS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee and carry out the company’s mission statement across the flagship warehouse location.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Uphold company core values in all dealings with vendors, customers, sales teams, and internal departments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assume accountability for balancing customer delivery demands with company policies for cost containment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage, support, and nurture the development, growth, and success of Warehouse Managers, warehouse personnel, and drivers across multiple locations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create, build, and maintain the highest level of respect and loyalty with employees throughout the LA distribution center through firm, fair, and consistent leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strive to exceed company goals for profit production while containing warehouse and delivery costs region-wide.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor inventory performance, including turnover, merchandise controls, customer and vendor returns, and product quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all deliveries across the region are completed in a timely and cost-efficient manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;VENDOR RELATIONS AND COMMITMENTS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
